  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2022-06-23",
    "date": "2022-09-10T20:10:47Z",
    "text": "Digital Citizenship and Media Literacy Act\n\nThis bill directs the National Telecommunications and Information Administration to award grants to state and local educational agencies, public libraries, and qualified nonprofit organizations to develop and promote media literacy and digital citizenship education for elementary and secondary school students.\n\nMedia literacy includes the ability to access relevant information, analyze media content, evaluate the accuracy of information, and make educated decisions based on information obtained from media and digital sources.\n\nDigital citizenship includes the ability to safely, responsibly, and ethically use communication technologies and to participate in the political, economic, social, and cultural aspects of life related to technology and the digital world."
  },
